      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage documents a new, more intense wave of attacks and a tactical sequence that turned another potential collapse into a held position. Key plot elements to add: hostiles adapted and probed the new perimeter; Florence provided real-time tactical coordination that prevented breaches (including the emergency secondary barrier and Remedy's chemical flood); Buddy improved as a combat-support sensor; major resource and personnel strain emerged (Runner injured, Remedy chemically exhausted, Velvet damaged, structural damage extensive); hostiles withdrew in an organized retreat to regroup and will likely return with revised tactics; Florence remains socially isolated despite being indispensable and agrees—reluctantly—to continue coordinating primarily for Kira; the group organizes overnight recovery, watch rotations, emergency repairs, and expects an extended siege. I consolidated earlier, now-moot minutiae into broader bullets (e.g., initial crash, SAM offline, biological container status, earlier assault tactics) and removed repetitive tactical step-by-step details, keeping only plot-relevant outcomes and ongoing problems.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle carrying mining/terraforming supplies and a container labeled 'Biological Samples' struck the hull during approach and crashed; Kira Voss survived while several crew died.
          - Shipboard AI SAM remains offline; Kira’s neural link activated an assistant AI (Buddy); external communications and the ship’s distress beacon are broken.
          - Hull breach exposed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; a local plant collective found Kira, sheltered her, and used the crashed shuttle as temporary shelter.
          - The active Biological Samples container continues to glow, draw power, and cannot be shut down.
          - Remedy (salvage-built humanoid doctor) treated Kira’s leg; cooperative caregiving among the plants improved her condition and the collective moved toward self-reliance after outside help failed.
          - Scouts discovered deliberate hostile boundary markings; a coexistence delegation was rejected and hostile plants mobilized an organized, multi-directional assault.
          - Hostile forces used coordinated tactics—spore clouds, corrosive vines, projectile thorns, and subterranean root attacks—causing heavy structural damage and airborne hazards; Buddy and Scout provided crucial sensor and baiting support.
          - Initial defenses were fragmented until Florence, an exiled tactical node, offered conditional guidance; she directed contraction to a fortified inner perimeter and assigned roles (Velvet inner barrier, Remedy anti-spore, Runner root interdiction, Holloway comms), which stabilized the defense.
          - Hostiles adapted to the new perimeter; Florence read and predicted their probes in real time, and the collective adapted under her coordination to block multiple breach attempts.
          - A major underground root surge threatened to split the core defenses; Velvet erected an emergency secondary floor above Runner, Runner delayed the root, and Remedy flooded the gap with chemicals—together they forced the root to withdraw and prevented a collapse.
          - The battle became a war of attrition: after hours of waves the group held but suffered serious strain—Runner is injured and exhausted, Remedy’s chemical counter-agents are nearly depleted and cannot produce healing compounds until regenerated, Velvet is heavily damaged, supplies and structural integrity are low.
          - Hostile plants performed an organized, staged withdrawal to regroup and will likely return with revised tactics; Florence predicts an extended siege rather than quick assaults.
          - Florence remains socially isolated and emotionally excluded despite being essential; Holloway and others give reluctant, formal acknowledgment and request she continue coordinating; Florence agrees to help, explicitly for Kira's sake.
          - The group organizes overnight recovery: emergency medical treatment for Runner, minimal defensive perimeter maintained, watch rotations, prioritize structural repairs and resource recovery, and prepare for renewed, prolonged attacks tomorrow.
        </summary>
